  "instructions": [
    "Heat a pan over medium heat and add cumin seeds. Once they begin to crackle, add onion and garlic. Sauté until onions are translucent.",
    "Add bell peppers, coriander powder (cumin), and tamarind paste. Stir well, adding lime juice slowly to prevent burning. Mix thoroughly.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and let it simmer for about 5 minutes until the vegetables become soft and the flavors blend together.",
    "Mix in cilantro and sesame oil with a good stir. Taste test and adjust seasoning if needed (considering low-sodium ingredients).",
    "Serve immediately over steamed rice or as a side dish."
